Here’s a basic configuration for a Chart.js line chart with two data series. I’ve made up some sample data points for each series.

```javascript
const config = {
  type: 'line',
  data: {
    labels: ['January', 'February', 'March', 'April', 'May', 'June', 'July'],
    datasets: [
      {
        label: 'Series 1',
        data: [10, 15, 13, 20, 17, 22, 25],
        borderColor: 'rgba(75, 192, 192, 1)',
        backgroundColor: 'rgba(75, 192, 192, 0.2)',
        fill: true,
        tension: 0.4,
      },
      {
        label: 'Series 2',
        data: [8, 12, 14, 18, 15, 19, 24],
        borderColor: 'rgba(255, 99, 132, 1)',
        backgroundColor: 'rgba(255, 99, 132, 0.2)',
        fill: true,
        tension: 0.4,
      }
    ]
  },
  options: {
    responsive: true,
    plugins: {
      legend: {
        position: 'top',
      },
      tooltip: {
        mode: 'index',
        intersect: false,
      }
    },
    interaction: {
      mode: 'nearest',
      axis: 'x',
      intersect: false,
    },
    scales: {
      x: {
        title: {
          display: true,
          text: 'Months'
        }
      },
      y: {
        title: {
          display: true,
          text: 'Values'
        },
        beginAtZero: true
      }
    }
  }
};

// Assuming you have a canvas element in your HTML with id="myChart"
const ctx = document.getElementById('myChart').getContext('2d');
const myChart = new Chart(ctx, config);
```

### Explanation

- **`labels`**: Represent the x-axis categories, in this case, months.
- **`datasets`**: Each dataset represents a data series, with customizable properties like `label`, `data`, `borderColor`, `backgroundColor`, and `fill`.
- **`options`**: Set up to be responsive, with a legend, tooltip configuration, and axes titles.
- **`tension`**: Adds a curve to the line; set to 0 for straight lines if preferred.

This configuration should create a smooth line chart with two series, each filled with a slightly transparent color.

